Tonye Anyanwu has gifted 10 widows and orphans with fund capital to start a business after his just concluded entrepreneurship training workshop designed to train and empower 20 indigenes of Rivers State. The entrepreneurship training workshop was funded by Tonye Anyanwu and organized by the Connectopia Foundation. All the participants also received seed money and startup materials to help kick start their small scale business with skills acquired during the training workshop. Anyanwu says he is committed to helping not just widows or the less privileged, but also mentoring and helping small scale businesses and entrepreneurs through his foundation. The lucky 10 beneficiaries are the latest recipients of the Foundation’s support initiative. The foundation is the brainchild of Tonye Anyanwu who is the CEO & Founder of technology solutions company, Connectopia Tech LLC based in Dubai. Tonye Anyanwu’s impact via the Connectopia Foundation has been felt by everyone both young and old.